7. Data Acquisition System (DAQ): This is the system that receives the conditioned analog signal and samples it at the specified rate of 1000 samples per second. The DAQ is only responsible for acquiring the signal; it cannot be altered or tuned, thus necessitating the above signal conditioning steps.
